Name: Beck Head Stream Cave
ShortDescription: 19th?C lead mine featuring intact engine house, 50?ft chimney, gunpowder magazine, forge, shaft and inclined plane portals
LongDescription: Developed from 1842 by Duke of Devonshire. Peak production ~804?t in 1850, averaging ~470?t/y 1840–70. Closed 1881; reopened for barytes 1920s–30s (19?600?t recovered). Final mining 1958. Structures Grade?II listed.
RouteHazards: Warnings: Unstable structures; steep shafts; no public lighting or barriers  RouteHazards: Loose masonry, unguarded shafts, uneven ground  FloodRisk: Minimal; no active water inflows reported, but deep adits may contain hidden pools  EmergencyExits: None formal—entry should be visual only; underground access strongly discouraged
